args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject branding-related construct makes a positive, partial causal contribution to the success or outcome represented by the object (e.g., brand performance, memorability, or perceived success).
args.justification: The instance explicitly describes a positive, contributory causal role ("contributes to having a successful and memorable brand"), which is better captured by the predicate name "contributes_to" than the more generic "influences". Updating the canonical_rel_name and refining the description clarifies that this is a partial, enabling contribution to brand outcomes, while keeping the existing relation class and group (branding_impact_relation under CAUSALITY) intact.
